context: The Athletics Division of George Brown College provides various sports programs and recreation services at two locations: St. James (Building A, 6th Floor at 200 King St. E, Toronto ON M5A 3W8) and Casa Loma (Building C, lower level at 160 Kendal Ave., Toronto ON M5R 1M3). Students have access to these athletic centres based on their student status: full-time students have unlimited access included in their fees, while part-time students pay $60 per semester. Contact information for St. James inquiries is 416-415-5000 ext. 3336 and/or ext. 4714, and for Casa Loma inquiries it is 416-415-5000 ext. 6795 and/or ext. 6796. Services offered include general fitness programs. Students must register their student card at the beginning of each academic year to access these services. The athletic centres may be subject to closure or change without notice, and it is recommended that students verify George Brown College fee requirements for the most accurate information.
